 kim & chang in the white collar criminal defense practice group before joining the firm in 2007 she served as a public prosecutor for 10 years developing expertise in a wide range of criminal law matters and was awarded honors by the korean government including the titles of public prosecutor general 2003 and cabinet minister of the ministry of justice 2006 lee completed her master's work in competition and antitrust laws at the graduate school of legal studies at korea university in 2006 she has extensive experience in white collar criminal defense primarily in the areas of securities fraud insider trading and other corporate crimes including fair trade regulation downloads audio audio lee presentation streaming mp3 location philippines conference room encina hall 616 serra st 3rd floor stanford university stanford ca 94305 directions map fsi contact heather ahn topics south korea search ksp events of interest korean food korean identity the impact of globalization on korean agriculture john feffer the influence of the investigation of illegal 2002 presidential election funds on the politics and economy of korea ahn dai hee support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 724 8271 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
